    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah so it seems to say that <code>IsCompl x y</code> is true exactly twice (bot,top and top,bot, and bot isn't top).</p>",
        "id": 472527668,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1727194080
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes. But you could say that x or y is bot, but the module itself is not bot. As for irreducibility.</p>",
        "id": 472527829,
        "sender_full_name": "Antoine Chambert-Loir",
        "timestamp": 1727194136
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Aha -- top isn't bot, but if top = x \\sup y with x \\inf y = bot then x = bot or y = bot. Makes it look like the definition of prime.</p>",
        "id": 472527966,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1727194194
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess <code>∀ x y, ⊥ &lt; x → x &lt; ⊤ → ⊥ &lt; y → y &lt; ⊤ → IsCompl x y → False</code> would work?</p>",
